good markdown-style syntax for a collaspible section, concise



A clean Archangel-style option:

+++ title="evidence details"
This section is collapsed by default.
It can contain:
- testimony
- photos
- documents
- links
+++

More explicit:

:::collapse title="minority report" default="closed"
The strongest unpopular counter-evidence goes here.
:::

Best recommendation:

:::section title="evidence details" collapsed="true"
content here
:::

Why this is good:

:::section title="..." collapsed="true"
...
:::

* readable
* markdown-ish
* easy to parse
* supports attributes later
* can become HTML <details>
* works for claims, evidence, testimony, timelines, and public figure notes

Example in Archangel syntax:

# claim: nuclear power is necessary for climate stability
summary:
Nuclear power may be needed to provide reliable low-carbon energy.
:::section title="counterclaim" collapsed="false"
Renewables, storage, transmission, and demand response can replace fossil fuels without expanding nuclear power.
:::
:::section title="minority report" collapsed="true"
Some environmentalists support nuclear power because they believe climate risk is greater than nuclear risk.
:::
:::section title="evidence" collapsed="true"
- [ev#grid-reliability-study]
- [ev#nuclear-cost-overruns]
- [ev#france-low-carbon-grid]
:::






